    {
      "label": {
        "none": [
          "Key People and Groups"
        ]
      },
      "value": {
        "none": [
          "National Science Foundation",
          "Colorado State University",
          "Environmental Protection Agency",
          "Sierra Club",
          "Rocky Mountain Center on Environment"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "label": {
        "none": [
          "Historical Context"
        ]
      },
      "value": {
        "none": [
          "The Winter Orographic Cloud Modification Experiment was proposed by the National Science Foundation to investigate the potential for cloud seeding to increase snowpack in the Rocky Mountains. While ski areas welcomed the project for its potential benefits, environmental groups expressed concerns about the ecological impacts and the toxicity of silver iodide on local ecosystems. The mixed community reactions highlighted the tension between economic interests and environmental protection."
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "label": {
        "none": [
          "Completed"
        ]
      },
      "value": {
        "none": [
          "Incomplete"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "label": {
        "none": [
          "Notable Quotes"
        ]
      },
      "value": {
        "none": [
          "\"The experiments might be quite useful in providing warning of adverse effects which could come from later sustained, widespread, or intensive applications of the procedures being tested.\" — Sierra Club - Appendix D",
          "\"The acceptance of future programs by local residents might also be enhanced if this sensitive subject is handled properly.\" — Rocky Mountain Center on Environment - Appendix E"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
